<!--
VOICING PLAN — 'Twas On That Dark, That Doleful Night (F major / D minor)
==========================================================================
Same melody and chords as 4097 but with a contrasting voicing strategy
emphasizing quartal harmony, open spacing, and rhythmic variety throughout.

DIFFERENTIATION FROM 4097:
- Uses "44" quartal patterns (D G C, F Bb Eb) more often
- Wider LH spacing — stacked 5ths (D A D A) in register
- More quarter-note motion in harp rather than half-note blocks
- Sus4/sus2 voicings ("42"/"24") at phrase boundaries
- "332" third inversion patterns for color variety

PHRASE 1 (mm. 1-4): Quartal and open opening
- m1: "44" quartal D G on VIm (two 4ths up); V as C G open 5th
- m2: Ascending I arpeggio in RH (A C F quarter notes); LH "334" A2 E3 A3 C4
- m3: I "44" quartal in LH (F Bb Eb), IV "34" 2nd inv in LH (D G Bb F)
- m4: I sus4 "433" F Bb Eb half, then resolve to root F C F A

PHRASE 2 (mm. 5-8): Quarter-note motion, more rhythmic
- m5: All quarters in both hands; LH tracks chord changes beat by beat
- m6: I "332" 3rd inv and wide VIm (D F A E) — very open sound
- m7: I sus2 "24" (G C) in both hands, then V with wide LH (C G E C)
- m8: Ascending arpeggio in RH (F A C), then held C F open 5th

PHRASE 3 (mm. 9-12): Quartal revisited, maximum VIIø7 tension
- m9: I "44" quartal in LH (F Bb Eb), VIm quartal (A D G)
- m10: VIIø7 four-note LH; VIm five-note — maximum density at climax
- m11: VIm "43" 1st inv (F A D) in RH; 5-note LH on VIm
- m12: VIm quartal "44" in RH (D G C); pure 5ths in LH (D A D A) — ethereal

PHRASE 4 (mm. 13-16): Final convergence, maximum voices
- m13: I "333" maj7 in LH (F A C E), then 5-note VIm
- m14: IIm sustained whole in LH (G D G Bb); RH arpeggiates up
- m15: VIm "333" four-note in RH (D F A C); I "334" in LH
- m16: Final VIm five-note (D A D F A) — same as 4097 close but arrived
  via different path (quartal → open → minor convergence)

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS
========================
- LH bass note: D–A–F–F–D–F–F–F–F–E–D–D–F–G–D–D
  Same bass line as 4097 but inner voices take very different paths
- m3 beat 2: LH IV "34" second inversion (D G Bb F) — top voice G connects
  to G2 in m4 LH quartal — smooth inner voice
- m7 sus2 (G C): creates a bitonality moment — F pedal + GC above = suspended cluster
  Resolves to clean V (C E G) — effective suspension–resolution
- m14: LH whole G D G Bb (quartal + octave) while RH shifts up Gm → Bb

TEXTURE ARC
===========
- mm. 1-4:  Quartal/open. 2 RH, 3-4 LH. Austere and modal.
- mm. 5-8:  Rhythmic. All quarter notes. 3 RH, 4 LH.
- mm. 9-12: Full/thick. VIIø7 maximum at m10. 3 RH, 4-5 LH.
- mm. 13-16: Maximum. 4 RH + 5 LH at m15-16. Final minor close.
-->
